Fast-rising solo artiste, Ayeni Benjamin aka Razzy AG, has hinted that plans are in top gear to collaborate with top music stars in the nation’s music industry as part of the move to redefine the industry. The ‘calling’ singer hinted at plans to get one of the top-ranking artists on a collaboration project before the end of 2022 but refused to give the name of the act or acts he’s planning to work with. The gifted singer continues to soar since his emergence on the scene at a time when rap music is reported to be recording low patronage. The Ekiti-born musician had been with a music group known as Spartaz for many years before deciding to go solo.   How Eedris Abdulkarim predicted Burna Boy’s Grammy win, by…     Buga’s success has encouraged me to do more, Kizz Daniel     Yetunde Barnabas, Peter Olayinka expecting first child   Razzy AG has displayed his abilities in songs that include calling, make we dance, e go well, and Moonlight. The hairy and dark-skinned singer said he is leaving nothing to chance to see that rap music regains its position in Nigeria. He was spotted at the just concluded Africa Magic Viewers Choice Awards (AMVCA). It is however unconfirmed if the rapper is preparing to make an in-road into the movie industry.